rComments: Really fantastic lecturer- consistently good. Very approachable and clearly cares about his students. Highly recommend.
Very funny and caring professor, would love to have him again in the future.
he was one of the nicest profs for my online classes, as long as you take notes from the lecture slides, you're pretty much set. very well organized class and online atmosphere!
Professor Liboiron is a great teacher. His lectures were concise and engaging. Would recommend. His midterm and final weren't that hard either.

Chris is a beauty, definitely a hockey guy. He's pretty frank, but has a good sense of humour and is relatable. His class and tests are fairly easy if you take good notes. The DGDs are interactive and a lot of fun as well.
Great prof! for first-years made the transition quite smooth and was very helpful and fair with all the deliverables. highly recommended and I hope I have him later on as well.
Chris pulls no punches; what's taught in class will be on the exam and nothing more. Real easy to communicate with as well. Overall, the guys got class.
Chris is a really good prof and probably one of the best lecturers, his exams convey what was learned in class so if you study well you would have no problems. If you can take this prof take him

He was an amazing prof, really liked him. Not only was he good at teaching, his assignments were fairly graded and he seems to care about his students. I took a lot away from his class and hopefully I get him again.

Having a full course load online is taxing but Chris' class was the only one I thoroughly enjoyed and looked forward to. The expectations are very clear and he is very engaging. Read audit cases before class + attend class and take notes  you should be well prepared for your examinations.

Hands down one of the best lecturers at University of Ottawa. This was even more challenging given the course was online. Very caring professor as well- the midterm exam was completely messed up (not his fault) however a deferred exam or adjustment was offered. 100% will take Professor Liboiron again.
Very good lecturer. Given the troubles some have had with online courses he let us know participation was optional this term - and let us self assess. Lots of reading but overall a good experience.

Would not recommend taking Chris during online school. He refuses to check emails and is overall not helpful in his responses. I asked him a question and he replied two days later telling me to ask my tax prof when it was related to our course material. He is not accessible outside of lectures and expects you to work HARD for participation marks.

Midterm was filled with impossible to answer questions Group project had no marking criteria, impossible to access data, my group was missing members Prof was negative towards questions about midterm and project, didn't reply to emails about them either He's a fantastic lecturer, poor assessment administrator He is a part time prof and it shows

Genuinely cares about his students and is very helpful. Notes are clear and organized. No surprises on midterm or final. Class can be dull at times, but he tries his best. I wish all professors would be more like him. Would be happy to see his name again on my schedule
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Amazing prof, great lecturer, pick ur group wisely, as I got screwed big time due to his rules of allowing students to take up to 25% of your grade and assigning it to another group member cuz I did not know anybody and I joined a group of friends. Very clear grading criteria, nobody fails the class. Medium course load but rewarding! Participate!

One of the best profs I've taken in Telfer. Important to read the cases each week, participation counts. He's got tons of good stories and really makes audit a fun subject to learn about. The group seminar is a lot of work, make sure you pick a good group and start early. Midterm was fair!

Really helpful prof who actually wants you to succeed. Testsexams were harder than expected and were marked tough but he is very good for re-marking if you feel you deserved a higher grade. Read the textbook and do the assignments before class and it will be a breeze. Ask for help if you need it - he always stayed late after class to help.
He is very good at teaching, but his exams are weird and hard, even for the three quiz.
Great teacher. Interesting stories, and relates the subject matter to real-life scenarios. Definitely recommended.

An absolutely excellent professor! So far the best one I've ever had in my career. He is a wonderful speaker, explains very complex topics and in a way that it seems the easiest thing in the world! His examples from personal experience are very helpful and he funny too! I seriously felt like hugging him after the final exam.. take a class with him!
Interesting person

Great teacher, took the time to explain subject matter. He talks from much experience and has stimulating stories to tell. Tends to talk quickly at times but will start over if you ask him to. Very approachable, likely one of the best PT profs at Telfer.
Very good prof...he knows what he is teaching....recemmended
knowledgeable of his field. Seems to care
